						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab standing in the South-West corner of the compound of Madhukēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>16th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">16th Century A.D.,</hi> seems to register a gift of land, the details of which are all lost. It refers to some <hi rend="italic">nāyakas</hi> as witnesses of the gift.</p>						

						</summary>
